title: Roundup (Oct. 9): Gilman upsets No. 4 Loyola in boys soccer
text:
Roundup (Oct. 9): Gilman upsets No. 4 Loyola in boys soccer Soccer ball Tom Worgo Contact Reporter Baltimore Sun Media Group 
Senior midfielder Will Webb scored in the 18th minute on a shot to the left corner from 8 yards out after corralling a throw-in from junior forward Braeden Alevizatos to lead the host Greyhounds to a 1-0 victory over the Dons in a Maryland Interscholastic Athletic Association A Conference game. 
Gilman senior goalie Jake Young made 18 saves. 
The Greyhounds' 3-0 loss to Loyola on Sept. 11 in Towson was fresh on their minds heading into the rematch. 
"We were really fired to get some revenge against them, and to get back at them at our place is pretty satisfying," said Webb, whose team was outshot 24-3 on Friday. 


Football 
Liberty 12, North Carroll 0: A game that started an hour late because of a thunderstorm and was scoreless at halftime was decided by a field goal by Brendan Bird, a touchdown pass from Ben Agostino to Jarrett Pfeifer, and a safety.
